# Trivy container-image allowlist
#
# This file documents HIGH/CRITICAL vulnerabilities detected in the
# smart-erp-next runtime image that are inherited from the upstream
# postgres:18-alpine base image or from build-time dependencies copied into
# the production image. They are tracked and should be removed by updating the
# base image / dependencies, not by expanding this list.
#
# See: https://github.com/hieuck/Smart-ERP-Next/issues/554

# Go stdlib CVEs in postgres:18-alpine base-image binaries (gosu, initdb helpers,
# docker-entrypoint scripts). The custom entrypoint uses `su`, so gosu was removed
# in the Dockerfile, but other Postgres utilities still bundle an older Go runtime.
CVE-2023-39325
CVE-2023-45283
CVE-2023-45288
CVE-2024-24790
CVE-2024-34156
CVE-2025-61726
CVE-2025-61729
CVE-2025-68121
CVE-2026-25679
CVE-2026-27145
CVE-2026-32280
CVE-2026-32281
CVE-2026-32283
CVE-2026-33811
CVE-2026-33814
CVE-2026-39820
CVE-2026-39822
CVE-2026-39836
CVE-2026-42499
CVE-2026-42504

# Node.js / pnpm / picomatch / sigstore CVEs detected in bundled build-time
# tooling. These packages are copied as part of node_modules and should be
# eliminated by pruning dev dependencies from the runtime image.
CVE-2026-33671
CVE-2026-48815
CVE-2026-50015
CVE-2026-50016
